; warm-start.fk — seed the Form-native CHALLENGER's first prototypes from the CHAMPION's early
; confident labels, so it begins learning from real ground truth instead of cold.
;
; champion-challenger.fk flips authority to the Form-native arm only once it has PROVEN it reaches the
; 3rd-party champion over a window — but a challenger that starts from nothing has to climb that window
; from a cold start, slow and noisy. This is the warm start that precedes the competition: before the
; challenger casts its first vote, hand it the champion's EARLY labels — but only the ones the champion
; named with real confidence. A timid label is not ground truth; seeding on it teaches the challenger
; the champion's guesses. So the seed set is a CONFIDENCE-GATED selection: keep the labels whose
; confidence clears a floor, drop the rest. Only earned champion certainty becomes the challenger's
; starting prototypes — the same "credit only what's proven" gate value-execution.fk puts on promotion,
; moved one step earlier onto seeding.
;
; A seed = (list label vector confidence): (nth s 0) the champion's label string, (nth s 1) the input
; vector it labelled, (nth s 2) the champion's integer confidence 0..100 in that label. ws-conf reads
; the confidence; ws-strong? gates one seed to 0/1 against a floor (meets-or-exceeds); ws-seed walks the
; seeds and CONSES through only the confident ones (recursion is the loop, cons builds the kept list —
; same filter spine as core.fk's filter / confidence-weighted-vote's cw-weight-for, but keeping seeds
; rather than summing weights); ws-count is how many survived = the size of the challenger's warm
; starting set.
;
; Honest lane: this is a CONFIDENCE FLOOR on the champion's labels, nothing more — it does not check the
; label is CORRECT (the champion is the ground-truth proxy; if the champion was confidently wrong, the
; challenger inherits that error), it does not dedupe vectors, and it does not cap the seed count. The
; floor is meets-OR-EXCEEDS (ge, not gt): a seed exactly at the floor seeds (the boundary is confident
; enough). Confidence is an integer 0..100 by the primitive set — a seed at confidence 0 never clears a
; positive floor (an unsure champion label cannot seed), and a floor of 0 keeps every seed.
;
; Proven by: form-stdlib/tests/warm-start-band.fk (three-way at validate.sh)

(do
    ; --- CONF: the champion's confidence in this seed = the 3rd element of (label vector confidence). ---
    (defn ws-conf (s) (nth s 2))

    ; --- STRONG?: does one seed clear the confidence floor (meets-or-exceeds)? Returns 0/1 explicitly so
    ;     the band can `eq` it — a bare comparison's boolean shape diverges across kernels, so wrap to an
    ;     integer here, the same way confidence-calibrate's cc-trusted? does. ---
    (defn ws-strong? (s floor) (if (ge (ws-conf s) floor) 1 0))

    ; --- SEED: the sublist of seeds confident enough to start the challenger. Walk the seeds; when a
    ;     seed's confidence clears the floor, CONS it onto the kept list, else skip it. Recursion is the
    ;     loop, cons is the builder — only confident champion labels survive into the challenger's
    ;     starting prototypes. (The filter spine of core.fk inlined per AUTHORING's self-contained rule —
    ;     every function this band touches is defined right here.) ---
    (defn ws-seed (seeds floor)
        (if (eq (len seeds) 0) (empty)
            (if (eq (ws-strong? (head seeds) floor) 1)
                (cons (head seeds) (ws-seed (tail seeds) floor))
                (ws-seed (tail seeds) floor))))

    ; --- COUNT: how many seeds survived the floor = the size of the challenger's warm starting set. ---
    (defn ws-count (seeds floor) (len (ws-seed seeds floor)))

    0)
